PolyDropBox
A Decentralized, Paid, Expiring File-Sharing Platform (WeTransfer + Dropbox + Web3)
4
🔥 What Problem PolyDropBox Solves

Today’s file sharing tools (WeTransfer, Google Drive):

❌ Centralized (accounts can be banned)

❌ No crypto payments

❌ No trustless proof of access

❌ No burn-after-download

❌ No ownership guarantees

PolyDropBox fixes this by making file sharing:

Decentralized

Time-limited

Pay-to-access

Cryptographically secured

Ownership-aware

🧠 Core Idea (Simple)

User uploads a file

File is encrypted + stored on IPFS (Pinata)

A share link is generated

Access is controlled by Polygon smart contracts

File auto-expires, auto-burns, or auto-locks

👉 You don’t trust PolyDropBox.
👉 You trust cryptography + blockchain.

👤 USER POV (Receiver / Downloader)
Step-by-step flow
1️⃣ User opens a PolyDropBox link

Example:

https://polydropbox.io/d/abc123


They see:

File name

File size

Sender info (optional)

Access rules:

Free / Paid

Expiry time

Download limit

2️⃣ Access Check (Smart Contract)

Before download:

App checks Polygon smart contract:

Is file still active?

Has it expired?

Has it already been downloaded?

Has payment been made?

3️⃣ Payment (if required)

User can:

Pay in MATIC / USDC

Or sign in with wallet

Smart contract:

Verifies payment

Unlocks access

4️⃣ Secure Download

File is fetched from IPFS

Decryption key is released only once

User downloads the file

If Burn-After-Download is enabled:

Access is permanently revoked

5️⃣ Verification (Trust Feature)

User can see:

File hash

Upload timestamp

Polygon transaction proof

This proves:

“This file existed at this time and was not changed.”

